Specifics about this infrastructure:
What is a server?
-It is a computer system that provides resourses and funtionality to other computers in a network.

What is the role of the domain name?
-It provides a address for a website in simple human-readable text form.

What type of DNS record www is in www.foobar.com?
-The CNANE (canonical) DNS record.

What is the role of the web server?
-It accepts http request from the browser and send back web contents via the http protocol.

What is the role of the application server?
-it accepts dynamic requests from the webserver, updates the the hosted file and interacts with the database inorder to send dynamic content to the browser.

What is the role of the database?
-It store and maintain data, provide access to the application server inorder to respond to a dynamic request from the browser.

What is the server using to communicate with the computer of the user requesting the website.
The http protocol.

The issues are with this infrastructure:
Single point of failure(SPOF)
- Given that the is only one server available, this could lead to the website becoming unavailable if the server is to be down.

Downtime when maintenance needed:
-During the maintenance period the website will be unavailble as the server will be down.

Scalability:
-Given that there is one server available this will limit the amout of traffic the server would be able to handle, and will result to a slow performance of the website or may be unresponsive.
